All,

Attached is the script again.

Per my conversation with [Redacted], it does seem like [Redacted] is going to try and
screw with us on the residuals. Specifically, he has communicated to [Redacted] a desire to
begin interpreting “net revenue” in the IS0 agreement differently than he has at any
point in the last five years. He also communicated this during the 50/50 IS0 dispute
we had with him. He is essentially saying that if a merchant is on interchange plus
pricing and the interchange is 2.0% and our buy rate is 2.0% - and we charge the
merchant 2.20% that the .20% markup is not all ours. He wants to deduct all of his
“costs” that are already baked into the buy rate, such as his assessment costs,
network fees, etc. This would imply he nets nothing from a transaction and we give
him a % of our markup. It’s absurd and totally inconsistent with the agreement or
how it has ever been interpreted. It could cost us $200-400k/month in residuals. I
spent $50k fighting him the last time he tried this crap while we were 50/50
partners on a small portfolio.

I do think we should have [Redacted] call to see if [Redacted] is making the same
indication to him so it doesn’t look like we are all coordinating. Can you give him a
call after you review this?

Also, I removed the sentence near the end of the movie script about “we need
consideration for the effort we put into this” or words to that effect. I think it could be
misinterpreted.

Thanks,
[Redacted]
